bow-strings are made; 3. bow-string.

<span id="fn_382"></span>[143:8](sbe20044.htm#fr_389.md) Pavananto ti
pâsanto (B.).

<span id="fn_383"></span>[143:9](sbe20044.htm#fr_390.md) Vidho. But both
the reading and the explanation are uncertain, and Buddhaghosa says
nothing. The word occurs also, and apparently in the same sense, in the
Old Commentary on the 86th Pâ*k*ittiya.

<span id="fn_384"></span>[144:1](sbe20044.htm#fr_391.md) Sa*m*ghâ*t*iyo in
the plural must mean garments and not waist-cloths only. See the
parallel passage in the Bhikkhunî-vibhaṅga, Pâ*k*ittiya XCVI.

<span id="fn_385"></span>[144:2](sbe20044.htm#fr_392.md) Ga*nth*ika*m*. The
